description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced registered nurse to join the senior nursing team on Lister 1 as a full time Deputy Sister/Charge Nurse. Lister 1 is a developing area, and we see on average 500 patients per month. Elective oncology and urology patients attend Lister 1 for procedures and infusions including TWOC’s, interventional radiology procedures, immunotherapies, blood transfusions, and central line care to name a few. We also assess acutely unwell patients and patient&#39;s experiencing side effects from their treatment, and aim to prevent admissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, dynamic and committed Deputy ward manager and will welcome any forward thinking, caring individual with experience of leading a team who is committed to providing a high standard of safe quality patient care. Experience of teaching and developing services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience within oncology and or urology is an essential prerequisite for this post and having strong oncology / urology foundations will provide a solid base on which you can further develop your leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must display excellent leadership and communication skills and be confident to deal with members of the public and the hospitals multidisciplinary team. It is essential that you have recent experience in an acute environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be required to support staff and take an active role in band 6 management duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are keen to encourage developments in line with Trust policy and working in new ways. We recognise responsibility to ensure that staff are developed and stimulated within their environment in order to achieve vision and deliver care that reflects the values and behaviours of the Trust. We offer excellent opportunities for career progression, training and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are highly recommended.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name-Rebecca Childs&lt;/p&gt;
